	(text "Design Notes"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 17.018 131.826 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 3.302 3.302)
				(thickness 0.6604)
				(bold yes)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "2a1e7f96-fbad-4d58-afec-2c2f677ffec2")
	)
	(text "- The TPS4H160AQPWPRQ1 allows a max current output of 2.5A across all channels\n- One IC should be for hazards, brakes, reverse, front indicators (each 1 channel)\n- Second IC should be for turn signals (two channels), DRL, and horn\n- The voltage supply pins on each IC are internally tied, do not require separate\n  caps for each\n- Rser is dependent on voltage from high channel pins (our MCU is 3.3V so a 4.7k resistor\n  works best, for a 5V MCU would be 10k)\n- The duplicate OUT pins give out an error. A single pin itself cannot handle the current \n  in case of a high enough amount therefore both pins should be connected together, basically\n  ignore the ERC\n- Rcl (resistor for current limit) is given by formula Vcl*Kcl/Iout where Vcl\nis voltage for the pin (0.8V) and Kcl is current limit ratio (2500) both given by datasheet\nwhereas Iout is desired max curremt limit (800 for default current limit of 2.5A)\n- PAD pin is a thermal pad to be connected to either device GND or floating\n- SEL and SEH are one-bit pins for specifying which channel to select to enable the current sensing for"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 17.78 138.938 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "ab7f1046-4df7-4ae8-87d0-3cec26eea2d2")
	)
